<span class="headers">Learn Tailoring</span>
<p>
<table>
<tr>
<td>
<a href="http://www.gucomics.com/archives/view.php?cdate=20001224"><img src="http://www.eqtraders.com/images/articles/gu_12242000.jpg" width="200" height="300" border="0" align="left" /></a>
</td>
<td>
<p>Tailoring is the art of working with pelts, hides, and silks in order to make armor and various containers. It is one of the easier skills to get started, but one of the hardest tradeskills in which to grandmaster. Three races (halflings, wood elves and erudites) also have tailoring as their cultural specialty.
<ul>
<li><a href="http://www.eqtraders.com/articles/article_page.php?article=g110&menustr=040110000000">How to Become a Mistress Tailor</a> - by Sinuuyanea Nocturne of Quellious</li>
<li><a href="http://www.eqtraders.com/articles/article_page.php?article=g111&menustr=040110000000">Myrron's Beginner's Guide to Tailoring</a> (last updated April 11, 2004)</li>
<li><a href="http://www.eqtraders.com/articles/article_page.php?article=g112&menustr=040110000000">A Non-Tailor's Guide to Getting Tailored Velious Armors</a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.eqtraders.com/articles/article_page.php?article=g286&menustr=040110000000">LoY Robes for Post-187 Skilling</a> by Nichola Smith</li>
<li><a href="http://www.eqtraders.com/recipes/recipe_page.php?article=62&rsa=Tailoring&sb=item&sub=other&menustr=080110000000">Tailoring Recipes</a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.eqtraders.com/sources/source_trade_page.php?st=Tailoring&menustr=110130000000">Tailoring Supplies</a></li>
</ul>
</td>
</tr>
